==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piles
<hw>Piles</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pila</ets>
a ball. Cf. <er>Pill</er> a medicine.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The
small, troublesome tumors or swellings about the anus and lower part of
the rectum which are technically called <altname>hemorrhoids</altname>.
See <er>Hemorrhoids</er>. <note>[The singular
<singw><it>pile</it></singw> is sometimes used.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Blind piles</b></col>, <cd>hemorrhoids which do not
bleed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pileus</ent>⟦br⟧
